Rocket Jump Limited - Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 22nd January 2020
​
Thank you for playing our games!
This Privacy Policy describes:
The ways we collect personal data about you and why we do so
How we use your personal data, and
The choices you have about your personal data.
This Privacy Policy applies to games, websites and related services from Rocket Jump Limited, which we here collectively call the Service. Your continued use of the Service after the effective date will be subject to the new Privacy Policy.
The Data We Collect
Data we collect automatically
Game progress, gameplay data and analytics
Your IP address and advertising ID
Data about your device, such as device name and operating system, browser type and language
General location data
Data we collect from our partners
Data we receive if you link a third party tool with the Service (such as Game Center, Google Play Games alias, Facebook)
Data from platforms that the games run on (such as to verify payment)
Data for advertising and analytics purposes, so we can provide you a better Service
Data you provide us
Name and email address if you login to our games, choose to sign up to our marketing communications, or if you contact us via email.
Why Do We Collect Your Data
To make the Service work
To perform the contract, we process data necessary to
Create accounts and allow you to play our games and use our Service
Operate the Service
Verify and confirm payments
Provide and deliver products and services you request
Send you Service related communications
​
To make the Service more suitable for our players
To provide a great Service to our players, we have a legitimate interest to collect and process necessary data to
Update and develop player profiles
Develop and improve the Service and player experience
Manage our relationship with you
Provide social features as part of the Service
Customise your Service experience
Respond to your comments and questions and provide player support
Provide you offers in the Service as well as by email
Send you related information, such as updates, security alerts, and support messages
Enable you to communicate with other players
​
To show personalised advertisements
To show you personalised advertisements in the Service we have a legitimate interest to process necessary data to
Use personal data to deliver ads based on your interests
Track the content you access in connection with the Service
Deliver, target and improve our advertising and the Service
​
For information on how to opt-out from personalised advertisements, see section ‘YOUR RIGHTS AND OPTIONS’ below.
​
To analyse, profile, and segment
In all of the above cases and purposes, we may analyse, profile and segment all collected data..
​
Who Can See Your Data
Apart from Rocket Jump Limited, your data can be accessed by others in the following situations:
​
Other players
Social features are a component of our games. Other players and users may, for example, see your alias and scores or achievements.
​
Partners working for Rocket Jump Limited
Rocket Jump Limited have partners who perform services for us. These partners process your data only at and according to Rocket Jump Limited's instructions to provide the Service, such as hosting, player support, advertising, analytics and fraud prevention.
​
Advertising and Social Media partners
When you use our Services, you might also use third party services, such as Facebook, Twitter and Game Center. We do not control how they interact with you and you should ensure that you consent to the terms of use and privacy policies offered by the third party services before providing them with your information. You acknowledge that we are not liable when third party services use information you provide to them.
We also work with certain business partners, such as other game developers and advertising partners, and information collected from you may be shared through these partnerships.
Some of our business partners are outside New Zealand. Below is a list of some, but not all, business partners that we actively share user information and usage data with (this list is subject to change):
